The Life Esidimeni ghosts that have been spooking former Gauteng health MEC Qedani Mahlangu are now gnawing at the prominent politician's finances. Sunday World can reveal that Mahlangu's lawyers JL Raphiri Attorneys who represented her at the Life Esidimeni arbitration hearings, have turned against her over her alleged failure to settle the more than R1.5m legal bill they put on her doorsteps for the services they rendered. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD.